VISIT NEWSHOUR.PBS.ORG.

22:10.496 --> 22:18.170
>> THIS IS PBS NEWSHOUR WEEKEND,
SUNDAY.

22:18.237 --> 22:19.605
>> Larson:
AN OPERA THAT IS OPENING

22:19.672 --> 22:21.473
AT THE LINCOLN CENTER FESTIVAL
IN NEW YORK ON THURSDAY

22:21.540 --> 22:24.944
HAD ITS U.S. PREMIERE AT THE
HOUSTON GRAND OPERA

22:25.010 --> 22:27.446
THIS PAST JANUARY, WHERE OUR
SISTER STATION,

22:27.513 --> 22:30.115
HOUSTON PUBLIC MEDIA,
SPOKE WITH SOME OF THE PEOPLE

22:30.182 --> 22:31.917
INVOLVED IN THE PRODUCTION.

22:31.984 --> 22:33.852
IT'S CALLED "THE PASSENGER"

22:33.919 --> 22:37.223
AND IT'S BASED ON A RADIO PLAY
AND NOVEL OF THE SAME NAME

22:37.289 --> 22:40.960
BY A CONCENTRATION CAMP
SURVIVOR, ZOFIA POSMYSZ.

22:41.026 --> 22:46.832
THE OPERA TELLS THE STORY OF TWO
WOMEN DURING THE HOLOCAUST...

22:46.899 --> 22:52.838
ONE, A PRISONER AT AUSCHWITZ;
THE OTHER, HER SS OVERSEER.

22:52.905 --> 22:56.242
>> IT'S INTERESTING THAT ZOFIA
POSMYSZ HERSELF SAID

22:56.308 --> 22:58.811
WHEN SHE FIRST HEARD THE OPERA
THAT SHE DIDN'T THINK

22:58.877 --> 23:03.182
ANYONE COULD EVER CAPTURE
THE EXPERIENCE OF WHAT,

23:03.249 --> 23:06.418
NOT A DAY IN AUSCHWITZ WAS LIKE,

23:06.485 --> 23:09.421
BUT WHAT 15 MINUTES IN AUSCHWITZ
WAS LIKE.

23:09.488 --> 23:14.126
SHE SAID YOU DIDN'T TRY TO THINK
ABOUT SURVIVING FOR A DAY.

23:14.193 --> 23:17.796
YOU TRIED TO THINK ABOUT HOW TO
GET THROUGH THE NEXT 15 MINUTES.

23:17.863 --> 23:22.668
>> THE FACT THAT WHAT YOU'RE
WITNESSING IS A HUMAN STORY

23:22.735 --> 23:26.572
ABOUT TWO YOUNG GIRLS,
AND THESE GIRLS SHOULD HAVE MET

23:26.639 --> 23:30.109
IN A UNIVERSITY CANTEEN AND
SQUABBLED ABOUT A BOYFRIEND

23:30.175 --> 23:33.145
AND HELPED ONE ANOTHER WITH
THEIR ESSAY,

